blog.name: sunniebelle
blog.title: SunnieBelle
blog.description:
I'm a Texas-born-and-raised southern gal.
Just recently I was introduce to the incredible world of Doctor Who and immediately fell in love with it! I am a hard-core shipper of the Doctor and Rose Tyler, and especially of the 9th, 10th and/or Tentoo Doctor and Rose.
I'm also a huge fan of Scott Westerfeld's "Leviathan" trilogy! (btw: If you haven't read this series, I highly recommend them to people of any age. They are amazing!)
I love any shade of purple, all things horses and adore the sound of the violins and cellos together.  I'm an amateur writer and love to use my over-active imagination. I'm also an amateur artist, mostly pencil drawings. Go check out my artwork and original stories, if you would like to, on www.deviantart.com/sunniebelle You can also find me on fanfiction.net, TSP, and A03 where most of my DW and Leviathan fics are. :)

summary: Ok, just watched the first episode of Broadchurch!
body:
Ok, just watched the first episode of Broadchurch!

(For anyone who hasn’t seen it, there may be spoilers ahead!)

My initial thoughts on the episode is that it is intensely gripping and sucked me in right away and I will likely be binge-watching the first season! Lol :) I love the little bits of humor that were thrown in to lighten the mood of the show.

DT as Hardy was very captivating! He showed he knows what he’s doing, he means business and don’t ever cross him. I’m interested in seeing what Sandbrook has to do with his past, as it seems like a sore spot for him.

Olivia Colman and Jodie Whittaker were amazing! I just CRIED when Beth found her son on the beach and then was told it was in fact him. Oh, what a heart-wrenching portrayal.

I must say I was infuriated when I saw Olly post that Twitter post. So very disrespectful to the family and their grief! I get the impression though that it’s about to get worse.

Anyway, on to episode 2! (Just curious, would anyone be interested in hearing my thoughts on the next episodes as I watch them? Let me know if I should keep posting or not, and it’s ok if you tell me to shut it. :D )
